{"id":4919,"date":"2026-02-08T11:56:05","date_gmt":"2026-02-08T06:26:05","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/?page_id=4919"},"modified":"2026-02-08T11:57:34","modified_gmt":"2026-02-08T06:27:34","slug":"brhad-bhagavatamrta-4","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/brhad\/japan\/part-4\/","title":{"rendered":"Brhad Bhagavatamrta &#8211; 4"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n <iframe title=\"Evening class by Bhanu Swami (8th Dec 2017)\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/bwELrn2yWBA?start=2094&#038;feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>Brhad Bhagavatamrta -4 | HH Bhanu swami Maharaj | ISKCON Japan | 8th Dec 2017<\/strong><br><br>jaya r\u0101dh\u0101-m\u0101dhava ku\u00f1ja-vih\u0101r\u012b<br>gop\u012bjana-vallabha giri-vara-dh\u0101r\u012b<br>ya\u015bod\u0101-nandana vraja-jana-ra\u00f1jana<br>yamun\u0101-t\u012bra-vana-c\u0101r\u012b<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Hare K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a Hare K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a Hare Hare<br>Hare R\u0101ma Hare R\u0101ma R\u0101ma R\u0101ma Hare Hare<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Jaya Prabhup\u0101da Jaya Prabhup\u0101da &nbsp;<br>Prabhup\u0101da Jaya Prabhup\u0101da<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">nama o\u1e41 vi\u1e63\u1e47u-p\u0101d\u0101ya k\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a-pre\u1e63\u1e6dh\u0101ya bh\u016b-tale<br>\u015br\u012bmate bhaktived\u0101nta-sv\u0101min iti n\u0101mine<br>namas te s\u0101rasvate deve gaura-v\u0101\u1e47\u012b-prac\u0101ri\u1e47e<br>nirvi\u015be\u1e63a-\u015b\u016bnyav\u0101di-p\u0101\u015bc\u0101tya-de\u015ba-t\u0101ri\u1e47e<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">jaya \u015br\u012b-k\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a-caitanya prabhu-nity\u0101nanda<br>\u015br\u012b-advaita gad\u0101dhara \u015br\u012bv\u0101s\u0101di-gaura-bhakta-v\u1e5bnda<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Hare K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a Hare K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a Hare Hare<br>Hare R\u0101ma Hare R\u0101ma R\u0101ma R\u0101ma Hare Hare<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HH B<\/strong><strong>h<\/strong><strong>anu Swami Mahara<\/strong><strong>j<\/strong><strong>:<\/strong><strong><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"436\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-111.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4921\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-111.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-111-300x145.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-111-768x371.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And then Gopa kumar began to tell his own story. \u00a0He was a cowherd in Vrindavan, and then he got a guru and the guru gave him the same mantra. So, before the guru could explain everything, he disappeared.\u00a0And then this boy began to chant this mantra, and he became completely absorbed in it, and he became detached, and he wandered away from Vrindavan, went to the place on the Ganga there, and was continually chanting.<br><br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"441\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-112.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4922\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-112.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-112-300x147.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-112-768x375.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"409\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-113.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4923\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-113.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-113-300x136.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-113-768x348.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, he met a brahmana who was worshipping a Shaligram. So the brahmana told him to go to this nearby city where there was a king, and the king was worshipping Vishnu in a very elaborate manner.\u00a0So\u00a0he went there.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"416\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-114.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4924\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-114.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-114-300x138.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-114-768x354.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So then the king died, but he made Gopa kumar the king, so he became king of that country.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"402\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-115.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4925\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-115.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-115-300x134.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-115-768x342.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"444\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-116.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4926\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-116.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-116-300x148.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-116-768x378.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But he also became a little bit disturbed by the features of it, because he couldn&#8217;t serve the deity directly.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"390\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-117.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4927\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-117.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-117-300x130.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-117-768x332.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So he gave up the kingdom, and he was still chanting the mantra. Then he met a devotees\u00a0from Puri who began to praise Jagannath. So, he went to Puri.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"443\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-118.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4928\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-118.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-118-300x147.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-118-768x377.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"405\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-119.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4929\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-119.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-119-300x135.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-119-768x344.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"477\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-120.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4930\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-120.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-120-300x158.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-120-768x406.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, he was pleased, but again he longed to serve the deity, but he couldn&#8217;t serve Jagannath. He met his guru again, and the guru encouraged him to continue chanting the mantra. Then the king died, and Gopa Kumar became the king of Puri\u00a0[Laughs].<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-121.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4931\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-121.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-121-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-121-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"422\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-122.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4932\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-122.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-122-300x140.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-122-768x359.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But he became dissatisfied because he couldn&#8217;t serve the deity directly, and also, he was doing so many kingly duties.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-123.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4933\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-123.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-123-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-123-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So he gave up the kingdom, and he was still there, but he didn&#8217;t want to leave because he was attached to Jagannath. So Jagannath himself ordered him\u00a0to go to Mathura and Vrindavan.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-124.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4934\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-124.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-124-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-124-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, he went back to Vrindavan, and there he was quite satisfied. But then he thought, I want to see Jagannath again, so he started to go back [Laughs]\u00a0to Puri again. But on the way, on the bank of the Ganga, he met some brahmanas. And these brahmanas began praising Swargaloka. The place above this earth, and that Swargaloka, the Lord directly resides.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-125.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4935\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-125.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-125-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-125-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So Vamanadeva appeared as the younger brother of Indra\u00a0there. So, he became very excited to see the Lord, so he began chanting his mantra.\u00a0So immediately, a celestial vehicle came down and took him to Swargaloka\u00a0[Laughs].<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-126.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4936\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-126.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-126-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-126-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, when he got there, he saw Vishnu sitting there. So, he was very satisfied, he offered his respects, and he offered prayers. And the Lord called out to him with a very compassionate voice.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-130.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4940\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-130.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-130-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-130-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So he\u00a0lived there for sometime, he\u00a0was very happy because he could see the Lord. But one time, Indra had a relationship with the wife of one great sage, and he got afraid and he disappeared\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0No, he had a relationship with some sage&#8217;s wife.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Devotee:<\/strong>\u00a0\u00a0Oh, Gopa kumar?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HH B<\/strong><strong>h<\/strong><strong>anu Swami Maharaj :<\/strong>No,&nbsp;No no&nbsp;Indra, Indra, Indra.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Devotee:<\/strong>&nbsp;Who disappeared?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj:<\/strong>\u00a0\u00a0Indra.\u00a0He hid himself.\u00a0So, then Brahaspati\u00a0ordered\u00a0the Devatas to install Gopu Kumar as Indra\u00a0[Laughs]. So, in spite of being the king, he didn&#8217;t stop his Japa, of\u00a0his Krishna Mantra, he continued to do that. And he began to think of Vraja again.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-128.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4938\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-128.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-128-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-128-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So though this Upendra lived in Swarga Loka, he couldn&#8217;t see him all the time. So, then he thought, I&#8217;ll go back to Puri and I&#8217;ll see Jagannatha all the time\u00a0[Laughs]. So he spent one Deva year there, which is 360 of our years, he spent there in Swarga Loka ruling as Indra\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-131.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4941\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-131.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-131-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-131-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then, when he was there, some sages from Mahar\u00a0Loka came down, Mahar\u00a0Loka is just above Swarga, so from the next highest planet, Mahar\u00a0Loka, some sages came down. And one can only attain that if one is even more pious than doing works for Swarga Loka. It&#8217;s much harder to get to Mahara Loka.So, though Swarga and all the lower planetary systems are destroyed at the end of Brahma&#8217;s day, Mahar\u00a0Loka and the planets above are not destroyed, they remain. So, in that place, the Prajapatis do sacrifices and the Lord is present to receive the offerings.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-132.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4942\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-132.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-132-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-132-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, he became very excited that he wanted to go to Mahara Loka, so he chanted his mantra, and then he ended up in Mahar\u00a0Loka. So there he saw the great sages doing sacrifices, chanting mantras, etc., and then he saw the Lord appear and accept those offerings.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-133.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4943\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-133.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-133-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-133-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So that place was very peaceful, and there were no faults there, there was no lamentation, no worry, because it&#8217;s not destroyed at the end of Brahma&#8217;s day. As long as they were doing the sacrifice, the Lord was present.\u00a0When the sacrifices were finished, the Lord disappeared\u00a0[Laughs]. So, this became a cause of unhappiness.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-134.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4944\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-134.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-134-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-134-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, though Mahar\u00a0Loka is not destroyed at the end of Brahma\u2019s Day, the fire for the lower three worlds begins to affect that planet and gets a little hot there\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0So then everyone has to move out of Mahar\u00a0Loka and they go to Jana Loka at night\u00a0time.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Jana Loka&nbsp;[Laughs]. &nbsp;So&nbsp;during Brahma\u2019s night time,&nbsp;that Janaloka and&nbsp;Tapoloka&nbsp;there people&nbsp;stay,&nbsp;everyone&nbsp;stays there&nbsp;in those planets but no sacrifice performed because Brahma&nbsp;sleeps also, and the Lord sleeps. So there&#8217;s no sacrifice. So they don&#8217;t see the Lord.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-135.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4945\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-135.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-135-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-135-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So one time, Sanat Kumara from Tapo\u00a0Loka appeared. And Gopa Kumar saw Sanat Kumara and was very impressed. So, Gopa Kumar was thinking, what kind of happiness they got there? Is it better than Mahar\u00a0Loka and Jana Loka? What does the Lord look like there? So he got very curious.\u00a0So, he chanted his mantra and he went there.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-136.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4946\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-136.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-136-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-136-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, Tapa Loka is a place where people who are very detached and renounced go, like sannyasis, etc.\u00a0And all the people there are basically in Jnana, fixed in samadhi, like yogis. And they all had mystic powers. But he couldn&#8217;t see the Lord there.\u00a0And by\u00a0the influence of the sages who are more or less\u00a0in samadhi\u00a0then his interest in the lord seemed to dwindle.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-137.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4947\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-137.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-137-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-137-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u00a0Out of respect for his Guru\u2019s order he continued\u00a0to chant his\u00a0mantra even though\u00a0he was little bit not so interested [Not clear].\u00a0So, because it was so peaceful there, he could concentrate on the mantra. And because he concentrated on his mantra, he desired to see the Lord more\u00a0even.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-139.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4949\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-139.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-139-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-139-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-140.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4950\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-140.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-140-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-140-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Of course, the sages there were saying, well, you don&#8217;t have to go anywhere. You just meditate and you&#8217;ll be satisfied.\u00a0You can see the Lord in your mind. This is the best thing. So, they praised the mind.\u00a0So why bother seeing the Lord? If your mind is happy with the Lord, then the senses automatically satisfied. So even if the Lord is not present visibly, still internally you can always be blissful\u00a0because you can see the Lord in the heart. Mind is the cause of the bliss,\u00a0not the\u00a0senses.<br><br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-141.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4951\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-141.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-141-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-141-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And they say that even in Bhakti\u00a0we have\u00a0nine types of devotional service\u00a0but\u00a0actually smaranam\u00a0is the most important.\u00a0And thus, it&#8217;s the most important of all the senses.\u00a0And even prema arises from the mind. The mind transforms in a special way and you experience prema. So it&#8217;s also a mental state.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-142.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4952\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-142.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-142-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-142-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br>So&nbsp;he did yoga&nbsp;and concentrated his&nbsp;mind and then&nbsp;he could see the lord everywhere.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-143.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4953\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-143.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-143-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-143-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And then\u00a0once\u00a0Brahma came to\u00a0Tapo loka riding on his\u00a0swan.<br><br><strong>Devotee :\u00a0<\/strong>In meditation\u00a0?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HH B<\/strong><strong>h<\/strong><strong>anu swami Maharaj<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>:<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong>&nbsp;No, no, actually he appeared in Tapaloka. He was going down to Pushkaradwipa. So on Bhumandala there is Mount Meru in the middle and Jambudwip&nbsp;and then we have different islands. And in the&nbsp;last island is Pushkaradwipa. Seventh island, sixth or seventh Island.&nbsp;And they worship Brahma there. So he was going to Pushkaradwipa. So then Gopa&nbsp;kumar&nbsp;thought, I should go to Brahmaloka&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;Because there, there is the Mahapurusha form of Vishnu. So he chanted his mantra in Samadhi. And then he ended up in Brahmaloka.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-144.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4954\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-144.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-144-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-144-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-145.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4955\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-145.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-145-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-145-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And there he saw the Mahapurusha, the Supreme Lord. So, he was very beautiful. He had thousands of arms, heads\u00a0and\u00a0feet\u00a0like universal form.\u00a0\u00a0And he was lying on Ananta-sesa.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-146.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4956\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-146.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-146-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-146-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So one time a demon had attacked.\u00a0So the Lord killed the demon. But Brahma, when he saw that demon, became very frightened. He disappeared\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0So, then the Lord assigned Gopa kumar to be Brahma\u00a0[Laughs]. For a little while\u00a0[Laughs]. So, this was a distraction, because then he had to do all Brahma&#8217;s duties.\u00a0And he couldn&#8217;t just look at the Lord all the time and serve the Lord. So, he became quite dissatisfied.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-147.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4957\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-147.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-147-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-147-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While he was residing there as the Brahma, then the scriptures personified.\u00a0They began having discussions in the assembly. All the personified Vedas were there, the Upanishads were there\u00a0and\u00a0the Puranas were there. And they would speak in the assembly of Brahma\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0 So, they were having a discussion about liberation. So, some of the Upanishads said that only by knowledge you can get liberation. No other means, only knowledge.\u00a0Other famous Upanishads and some of the Agama Sastras also said, no, you can get liberation by bhakti. So, they had some argument about this.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-148.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4958\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-148.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-148-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-148-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And then some other Upanishads, not the most famous ones,\u00a0but\u00a0something like Gopala tapani Upanishad\u00a0etc.\u00a0There\u00a0is some other Upanishads,\u00a0they\u00a0began to speak.\u00a0So they said, these Upanishads said that actually we speak about liberation, but we speak about it so that people can eventually reject it\u00a0[Laughs]. So in other words, these Upanishads are saying, we criticize liberation, we condemn it.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"453\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-149.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4960\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-149.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-149-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-149-768x385.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, they have a whole discussion of what is the happiness of liberation\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0So the happiness of liberation is the happiness like not being sick\u00a0[Laughs], in the absence of problems\u00a0[Laughs]. Or it&#8217;s like enjoying deep sleep. And so actually it&#8217;s not really liberation.\u00a0This term was created by people who were in illusion\u00a0[Laughs]. So even if you chant Namabhas, you can very easily get liberation. So that means it&#8217;s not very valuable at all.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"436\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-151.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4962\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-151.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-151-300x145.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-151-768x371.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you realize Atma, then you realize Brahman. And this Brahman is devoid of qualities, free from attachments, not changing, and completely inactive. This is liberation.\u00a0But Bhagavan has a body of eternity,\u00a0knowledge and bliss. He&#8217;s an ocean of the most excellent qualities.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"431\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-152.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4963\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-152.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-152-300x143.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-152-768x367.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, they describe that actually the Lord is both things.\u00a0He is this impersonal aspect of liberation, plus he&#8217;s full of all wonderful qualities. So, the Brahman, or the impersonal feature, is one Vibhuti or Shakti of the Lord. And the Supreme Lord himself is much more important than his Shakti.\u00a0So if you can realize Bhagavan, then you can get the highest bliss. So, the lotus feet of Krishna are like sugar. They&#8217;re joyful and they&#8217;re a source of joy. And Brahman is just joyful, but it&#8217;s not the source of the joy.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"440\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-153.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4964\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-153.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-153-300x146.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-153-768x374.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So this discussion took place and then Gopa Kumar understood that higher than liberation was realizing the Supreme Lord. So he was also discontented because as being the Brahma\u00a0there was a distraction for him.\u00a0So the Lord told him, you go to Mathura and there your desires will be fulfilled you can do your sadhana and you can go beyond Brahma Loka. If you want to stay in brahma Loka, you can\u00a0also go\u00a0higher beyond\u00a0the world\u00a0but you have to wait\u00a0till Brahma\u2019s life is ended. So that\u2019s going to be a long time,\u00a0so a bit quicker\u00a0if\u00a0you go back\u00a0to Mathura and do your\u00a0sadhana there.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"459\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-154.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4965\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-154.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-154-300x152.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-154-768x390.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Gopa\u00a0Kumar\u00a0left the Brahma Loka and he back down to Bhu mandala and he went to Vraja and everything else\u00a0had changed\u00a0because you\u00a0know it was so many\u00a0[Laughs]\u00a0days of Brahma\u00a0later but Mathura and Vrindavan was\u00a0the same.\u00a0And\u00a0then he met his\u00a0Guru again.\u00a0So the Guru taught him different, before he didn\u2019t teach many things.\u00a0He\u00a0just\u00a0gave the mantra and disappeared.\u00a0This time he began to teach him how to worship and meditate using the mantra. So, he said, by the power of this mantra you will know everything.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-156.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4967\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-156.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-156-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-156-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, he chanted and then he got a body which was beyond the material elements.&nbsp;He got a spiritual body. And then he began traveling through the universe. He went past swargaloka and all these different lokas, etc.&nbsp;And then he started going beyond the material layers of the universe. So, there are different layers beyond the universe after Brahma Loka, etc. of different elements starting with the earth element.&nbsp;But in that layer there is the earth devata and there is the form of the supreme lord and there is worship going on there also. So it&#8217;s not just earth,&nbsp;there is actually some worship going on in these different places.&nbsp;So Gopal Kumar began to look at all this.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"466\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-157.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4968\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-157.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-157-300x155.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-157-768x396.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, in the first covering that was the earth covering there he saw Bhumi Devi, the earth. She was worshipping Varaha.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"493\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-158.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4969\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-158.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-158-300x164.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-158-768x419.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And of course, he went beyond that layer, and he came to the water layer and there he saw Varuna&nbsp;worshipping Matsya&nbsp;[Laughs]. Going beyond that he went to the fire layer. And there Surya Narayan was being worshipped.&nbsp;Then he went into the air layer and Vayu was worshipping Pradyumna. Then he went into the ether layer and there&#8230; Who&#8217;s in charge of ether? Dig devatas maybe. And then they were worshipping Aniruddha. And then he went into the ahankara layer and there, I think they worshipped Sankarsana.&nbsp;And then in the layer of Maha tattva,&nbsp;Vasudeva was worshipped.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"452\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-159.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4970\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-159.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-159-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-159-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Layer\u00a0after layer after layer after and then he got to the layer of Prakriti\u00a0[Laughs].<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"507\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-160.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4971\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-160.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-160-300x168.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-160-768x431.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And Prakriti was worshipping Mohini Avatar.\u00a0And Prakriti, well\u00a0actually each layer he went\u00a0to\u00a0the\u00a0lord welcomed and said\u00a0you stay\u00a0here. But then\u00a0he said, no, no I\u00a0can\u2019t\u00a0stay.\u00a0\u00a0And finally, he got to Prakriti and Prakriti said OK, I can give you liberation.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"465\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-161.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4972\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-161.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-161-300x154.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-161-768x395.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>He refused to stay there and didn&#8217;t want liberation.He went beyond that layer of Prakriti, and he got to a place called Mahakalapura. This is the place of liberation. So the Lord was actually present in this place.\u00a0And therefore, he felt very happy. But this Lord was surrounded by effulgence. So, he wanted to see the deity of his mantra.\u00a0<br><br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"465\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-162.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4973\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-162.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-162-300x154.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-162-768x395.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And in this place Shiva and Parvati were residing. So they of course are great devotees of the Lord.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"769\" height=\"435\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-163.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4974\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-163.png 769w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-163-300x170.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 769px) 100vw, 769px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, while he was there he was a little bit disturbed because he almost merged into the Brahman [Laughs]\u00a0because it was all so\u00a0effulgent\u00a0everywhere.\u00a0\u00a0So he didn&#8217;t like it. It wasn&#8217;t very comfortable there. But then finally Vishnu dutas came back.\u00a0So these Vishnu dutas were only interested in bhakti. And these Vishnu dutas were going to the earth and other places within the material world and they were spreading bhakti everywhere. And they also saved the devotees when they were dying or even people who have nama bhasa like Ajamila they came and saved him.\u00a0So they go everywhere and\u00a0save people.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"492\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-164.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4975\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-164.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-164-300x163.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-164-768x418.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, Shiva began to describe about mercy. So, Brahma has some mercy but if you multiply that 100 times then that is the mercy of Shiva. You get to Shiva&#8217;s post.\u00a0And if you get 100 times more mercy than that you can go to Vaikuntha.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"477\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-165.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4976\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-165.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-165-300x158.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-165-768x406.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So if you want to reach Vaikuntha you should practice the nine types of devotional service. [Not clear]\u00a0the Bhagavatam and other scriptures.\u00a0And from those scriptures the pastimes of the Lord.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"444\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-166.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4977\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-166.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-166-300x148.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-166-768x378.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, Shiva was glorifying bhakti and the devotees. So, bhakti appears to be some function of the senses and the mind and the body in new people, in sadhana.\u00a0But advanced devotees consider the same activities that they are doing to be expressions of the Lord&#8217;s mercy. So, they do those actions without effort and without their own controls under the Lord.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-167.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4978\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-167.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-167-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-167-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Okay, so simply one should perform pure bhakti and particularly Nama Sankirtan.&nbsp;So actually, chanting the Lord&#8217;s name is much better than remembrance. Sankirtan is better than smaranam.<br><br><strong>Dev<\/strong><strong>otee <\/strong><strong>: <\/strong>That&#8217;s interesting.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HH Bh<\/strong><strong>anu<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;Swa<\/strong><strong>mi Mah<\/strong><strong>ara<\/strong><strong>j : <\/strong>So if you chant you are using the voice, you are also using the mind and you are also using the ear. So you are using many senses&nbsp;there. And this gives benefits to yourself and also gives benefits to other people.<strong><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"429\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-168.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4979\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-168.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-168-300x143.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-168-768x365.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If we control the sense of speech, then you can control the mind&nbsp;[Laughs]. So if you control your speech then you can also do better remembrance. So Nama Sankirtan produces proper remembrance.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"480\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-169.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4980\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-169.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-169-300x159.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-169-768x408.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Of course, it is also admitted that different people have different preferences,&nbsp;different likes and dislikes.&nbsp;So whatever devotional practice one favors that is best for oneself. So Sankirtan expands the joy of meditation and meditation expands the joy of kirtan.&nbsp;So they mutually support each other. So that actually one method only&nbsp;[Laughs].<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"473\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-170.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4981\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-170.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-170-300x157.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-170-768x402.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So if a person develops prema then he chants the name.&nbsp;&nbsp;That&#8217;s the sign of a person with prema. He does Sankirtan&nbsp;[Laughs]. So chanting the name is a practice but it&#8217;s also the goal Sadhya.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"534\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-171.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4982\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-171.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-171-300x177.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-171-768x454.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Okay so\u00a0we had the whole discussion with the [Laughs]\u00a0on Shiva loka, and then Vishnu dutas come etc. Like\u00a0that.\u00a0So Gopakumar goes back again to\u00a0Vrindavan again\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0He meets\u00a0his guru.\u00a0His name is given\u00a0here,\u00a0Jayanta,\u00a0that\u2019s his\u00a0guru.\u00a0There was Mahakalapura. He began\u00a0to perform bhakti, he got\u00a0prema\u00a0and was chanting the Lord\u2019s\u00a0name.\u00a0And then the Vishnu Dutas came\u00a0[Laughs]. And they said ok, now you can get a four armed form.\u00a0He had a spiritual form but it was a cowherd boy form, so you can\u00a0have a\u00a0four armed form like us but he\u00a0said\u00a0I\u00a0don\u2019t want that. So they take him on their vehicle and again he goes through all the worlds and through the coverings and he goes up Shiva&#8217;s abode and he goes past Shiva&#8217;s abode, this Mahakalapura and finally he goes to Vaikuntha.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"509\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-173.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4984\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-173.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-173-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-173-768x433.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Because he said you have to go back to earth if you want to go quickly\u00a0[Laughs]. \u00a0So it is described\u00a0that they took up him to Vaikuntha but and then he had to wait outside the gate.<br>And then the Vishnudutas\u00a0went inside and informed the Lord, so he was waiting outside the gate there. \u00a0So He saw many different servants entering in to that\u00a0gate\u00a0but they were\u00a0all\u00a0looking like Vishnu,\u00a0so he began\u00a0offering obeisances\u00a0and praising\u00a0them\u00a0you are\u00a0Supreme lord\u00a0and they kept\u00a0saying,\u00a0no,\u00a0no, no\u00a0we are not\u00a0and they covered their ears\u00a0etc. [Not clear]\u00a0making this mistake\u00a0they are all looking like Vishnu.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"495\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-174.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4985\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-174.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-174-300x164.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-174-768x421.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>They\u00a0also\u00a0had\u00a0the power\u00a0to take any form, so they could appear as tree,\u00a0or as a bird\u00a0or an animal\u00a0or as human being or as devata\u00a0etc.\u00a0They could take any form they wanted. So, they take these forms for the Lord&#8217;s pastimes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"388\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-175.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4986\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-175.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-175-300x129.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-175-768x330.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And finally the Vishnu dutas came back and they led him through the different gates and each time he saw the doorkeepers he thought they were also Supreme Lord\u00a0[Laughs]\u00a0but they weren&#8217;t\u00a0and finally, he met the Lord of Vaikuntha. So, when he saw the Lord, he became very ecstatic and happy.\u00a0And he identified this Vishnu form with the Lord of his mantra, Gopal. And he went to embrace the Lord.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"453\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-176.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4987\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-176.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-176-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-176-768x385.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But they had to stop him&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;So the Lord welcomed him very, very mercifully. So the Lord explains that actually I&#8217;ve been waiting for you for so long. So he was thinking maybe this lifetime He will come,&nbsp;in your next lifetime.&nbsp;So he was waiting and waiting and waiting.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>So then he explains, Vishnu explains that actually I became the guru, Jayanta\u00a0[Laughs].<br><br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"462\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-177.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4988\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-177.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-177-300x153.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-177-768x393.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br>So he was in Vaikuntha and he could have all these different powers, etc. but he avoided everything.\u00a0And he continued in his cowherd boy form.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"475\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-178.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4989\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-178.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-178-300x158.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-178-768x404.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So this caused a little bit of a problem because the other residents were saying you don&#8217;t look like us you should [Laughs]\u00a0actually look like everybody else\u00a0[Laughs]. And he would address the Lord as Gopal, etc.\u00a0and he would play his flute for him and dance like a cowherd boy, etc. So many of the residents were very embarrassed by that. So don&#8217;t do that\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0But other devotees there said no, actually the Lord is merciful to everybody and he&#8217;s satisfied with this as well.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"428\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-179.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4990\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-179.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-179-300x142.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-179-768x364.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So he felt a little bit discouraged there and he wanted to see the form of Krishna or Gopal. At the same time when he saw that form of Vishnu he felt respect and reverence.\u00a0So this caused some disturbance to him.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"479\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-180.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4991\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-180.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-180-300x159.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-180-768x407.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So then Narada Muni appeared and started giving him instructions. So he said that you can realize,&nbsp;you go to Vaikuntha,&nbsp;whoever goes to Vaikuntha realizes the same service to the Lotus Feet of Krishna from which he has developed taste.&nbsp;In other words, we do some we&#8217;re aspiring for a certain type of service we get that when we go to Vaikuntha. So according to the sadhana we do and what we expect as a form of the Lord we get that when we go to the spiritual world.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"471\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-182.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4993\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-182.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-182-300x156.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-182-768x401.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So in Vaikuntha actually the Lord has many forms because people worship in different ways&nbsp;as&nbsp;Varaha or&nbsp;Narasimha,&nbsp;so the Lord will assume those forms for different types of devotees.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some devotees are not attracted to just one form but they worship many forms.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"430\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-181.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4992\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-181.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-181-300x143.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-181-768x366.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And he says Krishna is one form but he&#8217;s different from Narayana. And you require a certain type of softness of the heart to appreciate this Krishna.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"488\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-183.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4994\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-183.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-183-300x162.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-183-768x415.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Still, different types of devotees are satisfied with different forms of the Lord and different degrees of happiness. So according to the worship, you get the result.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"464\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-184.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4995\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-184.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-184-300x154.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-184-768x395.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center has-large-font-size\"><strong>Q<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>&amp; A<\/strong><strong>:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Dev<\/strong><strong>ote<\/strong><strong>e :<\/strong>\u00a0Many times he became king, then he is supposed to learn, you know\u00a0[Laughs].<br><br><strong>H<\/strong><strong>H B<\/strong><strong>h<\/strong><strong>anu S<\/strong><strong>wami <\/strong><strong>Mahara<\/strong><strong>j :<\/strong>\u00a0Well in this way he could experience the full pleasure of each different place, like Brahmaloka, Indraloka, Earth planet, etc. But he was dissatisfied with it.\u00a0He gave it up.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Devot<\/strong><strong>ee 1<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;:<\/strong>&nbsp;Very much curiosity.<br><strong><br><\/strong><strong>Devo<\/strong><strong>tee 2<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;: <\/strong>Sanatana Goswami&#8217;s life work&nbsp;Maharaj?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HH B<\/strong><strong>h<\/strong><strong>anu Swami Maharaj:<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong>This is his big work.&nbsp;Of course the other one is Hari Bhaktivilas. Of course it says he actually wrote the first Sandarbhas, and then Jiva Goswami revised them.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1.<\/strong><strong>)<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>Siva resides in the Mahakalapura.<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>That&#8217;s not Kailash?<\/strong><strong><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HH B<\/strong><strong>h<\/strong><strong>anu Swami Maharaj:<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong>Kailash is on Earth, and then he has this Mahakalapura above Prakriti. Liberation [Not clear]&nbsp;Brahman.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Devotee:<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong>Is this Kailash here?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><br><strong>HH B<\/strong><strong>h<\/strong><strong>anu Swami Maharaj<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>:<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong>I&nbsp;guess so.&nbsp;And here Himalayas.&nbsp;Actually, this is in the wrong place. Brahmajyoti should be&nbsp;in [Not clear].<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2.<\/strong><strong>) <\/strong><strong>Gopakumar is the cowhe<\/strong><strong>r<\/strong><strong>d boy. In Vrindavan, originally? <\/strong><strong><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yeah, he was born there.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Devotee:<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong>He&#8217;s not an associate, a friend of Krishna.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HH B<\/strong><strong>h<\/strong><strong>anu Swami Maharaj:<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong>No, no, he&#8217;s just a regular cowherd.<br><br><strong>3.<\/strong><strong>) <\/strong><strong>Which time was <\/strong><strong>Gopakumar<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>living on Earth<\/strong><strong>?<\/strong><br><br>It must have been another day of Brahma.<strong>&nbsp;<\/strong>Because he spent some time in Brahmaloka, Maharloka&nbsp;and&nbsp;Tapaloka&nbsp;[Laughs], all these places. And that is a long time. He saw the whole day go by.&nbsp;So that\u2019s previous day, previous day&nbsp;like that.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4.<\/strong><strong>) <\/strong><strong>Maharaj, this is all composition. We have nine kind<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;of <\/strong><strong>pr<\/strong><strong>oces<\/strong><strong>s<\/strong><strong>.<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>Smara<\/strong><strong>na<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;is the most important. <\/strong><strong><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, that&#8217;s what the people on Tapaloka were saying, because they were involved in you&nbsp;know&nbsp;meditation. But then the Vishnu dutas they&nbsp;said, no&nbsp;[Laughs], Kirtan is &nbsp;the most important&nbsp;[Laughs].<br><br><strong>5<\/strong><strong>.) <\/strong><strong>M<\/strong><strong>ahara<\/strong><strong>j <\/strong><strong>t<\/strong><strong>his wo<\/strong><strong>rk<\/strong><strong>, d<\/strong><strong>oes it <\/strong><strong>loo<\/strong><strong>k lik<\/strong><strong>e <\/strong><strong>the <\/strong><strong>work <\/str